Parmalat, Risanamento, Terna: Italian Equity Market Preview

-- B y   E l i s a   M a r t i n u z z i
-- 
2011-06-01T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/parmalat-risanamento-terna-italian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close.  Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index (FTSEMIB)  added 318.27, or 1.5
percent, to 21,109.75.  Parmalat SpA (PLT)  : Italy’s biggest dairy company said
 Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP)  withdrew a list of candidates for Parmalat’s
board. Parmalat made the announcement in a stock-exchange
statement. The bank had proposed Parmalat Chief Executive
Officer Enrico Bondi in its board list.  The shares fell 0.2 percent to 2.58 euros.  Risanamento SpA (RN)  : The company said it extended
exclusive talks with a group led by Stefano Stroppiana which is
seeking to buy its Milan Santa Giulia real estate development.
The investor group includes China’s Super Ocean Real Estate Co.
Ltd. and Santo Versace, Risanamento said in a stock-exchange
statement. The shares fell 0.4 percent to 22.7 cents.  Terna SpA (TRN IM): The owner of  Italy ’s power grid said it
won’t seek to produce or sell energy in a way that would violate
the country’s laws and will work to resolve outstanding issues,
after the government ruled today it cannot generate solar
energy.  The shares rose 0.4 percent to 3.39 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisa Martinuzzi at 
